' plan-59-E: CONVERTED from `resource-collection-close-floated-invalid`.
'
' Used to assert that a binding whose ownership had floated to a collection could
' not itself close the resource (`TYPE_RESOURCE_INVALIDATE_NOT_OWNER`, retired).
' Under scope ownership the floated binding is still a pointer to the one
' resource and may close it; the collection's scope then finds it already closed
' and its own close is a defined no-op (plan-59-B's flag).
'
' Kept rather than deleted; only the verdict changed.
IMPORT collections
IMPORT fs

' Once a resource's ownership floats into an outer-scope collection it becomes
' a plain pointer: the binding may no longer close it (§15.6).
FUNC main AS Integer
  MUT handles AS List OF RES File = []
  MUT i AS Integer = 0
  WHILE i < 2
    RES f AS File = fs::openFile("tests/syntax/resources/resource-collection-close-floated-valid/src/main.mfb")
    handles = collections::append(handles, f)
    fs::close(f)
    i = i + 1
  WEND
  RETURN 0
END FUNC
